Text.Value: Perform Sleep Test
• While in the Rate mode, press and hold the RATE button and then press the ON/OFF button for approximately two (2) seconds
• The word "SLP" will be displayed
• The display will change to three dashes followed by the word "SLEEP"
• In the sleep mode, no rate will be displayed for approximately five (5) minutes
• After each five (5) minute interval, the Rate will be displayed for approximately one (1) second

Pre-Operation Test Procedures

Performing a Sleep Test

  • While in the Rate mode, press and hold the RATE button and then press the ON/OFF button for approximately 2 seconds or until the display becomes blank, except for a "SLP" indication.
  • Continue holding the buttons and the display will change to three dashes followed by "SLEEP".
  • Next, release both buttons and only the "SLEEP" will remain, indicating that the unit is in SLEEP mode.
  • There will be no RATE displayed for approximately 5 minutes, while in Sleep Mode.
  • After each 5-minute interval, the Rate will be displayed for approximately 1 second.
  • The unit will again go blank for the next 5-minute interval unless the Rate or Dose alarm set points are exceeded.
  • To return to Rate Mode, press and hold the ON/OFF button until the display returns to the Rate Mode display and the SLEEP indicator disappears.
  • Now that the Radiacmeter has returned to RATE MODE, it's ready for normal operation.
